[], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base class for an event (ie a frame) in a replay.\n\nAttributes\n----------\ntime_delta: int\n    The time since the previous event (ie frame).", "the osr format for non-std gamemodes isn't document on the wiki. Here's", "the reference I used for non-std replay events below:", "https://github.com/kszlim/osu-replay-parser/pull/27#issuecomment-845679072."]}, {"name": "osrparse.utils.ReplayEventOsu", "bases": ["ReplayEvent"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "osrparse.utils.ReplayEventOsu.x", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "osrparse.utils.ReplayEventOsu.y", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "osrparse.utils.ReplayEventOsu.keys", "type": {"name": "Key", "xref": {"fqname": "osrparse.utils.Key", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A single frame in an osu!standard replay.\n\nAttributes\n----------\ntime_delta: int\n    The time since the previous event (ie frame).\nx: float\n    The x position of the cursor.\ny: float\n    The y position of the cursor.\nkeys: Key\n    The keys pressed."]}, {"name": "osrparse.utils.ReplayEventTaiko", "bases": ["ReplayEvent"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "osrparse.utils.ReplayEventTaiko.x", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "osrparse.utils.ReplayEventTaiko.keys", "type": {"name": "KeyTaiko", "xref": {"fqname": "osrparse.utils.KeyTaiko", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A single frame in an osu!taiko replay.\n\n# Attributes\n\ntime_delta: int\n\n: The time since the previous event (ie frame).\n\nx: in